summary: Chelsea staged a dramatic late comeback to snatch a 3-2 victory at Nottingham Forest, with Nicolas Jackson scoring the winner in the 89th minute. The win keeps Chelsea in contention for a top-four finish, while Nottm Forest's survival hopes are all but over. Raheem Sterling and Reece James came off the bench to turn the tide for Chelsea after Forest had taken an early lead through Danilo and a Brennan Johnson penalty. Chelsea's victory was sealed when Jackson headed in a cross from James, leaving Forest all but mathematically relegated.

name: Rafael Nadal
summary: Rafael Nadal is preparing for the French Open, despite a recent loss in Rome. His match against Zizou Bergs was suspended due to a medical incident but has since resumed. Nadal has shown signs of improvement in his recent comeback win at the Italian Open, but his performance in Rome has raised questions about his readiness for the French Open. Despite this, he is still considered a contender for the title. Nadal's draw for the Rome tournament places him in the same quarter as Daniil Medvedev, while predictions anticipate a match between Nadal and Hubert Hurkacz in the fourth round. Nadal has expressed uncertainty about his participation in the French Open following his defeat to Hurkacz, but recent reports suggest he is making progress and trending upwards ahead of his likely final appearance in Rome.
